data.title: Jessie Wallace: EastEnders star reveals what happened to daughter and speaks out on police
data.meta_description: JESSIE WALLACE has spoken out about her experience with the police as the EastEnders star revealed her daughter was mugged in North London last year.
data.text:
“Police station closed/luxury flats. Not seen a real life policeman for years,” he went on.

“Gang continues… what happens next?”

Sharing the post with her own 70,000 Twitter followers, Jessie said: “This happened last year in Muswell Hill to my daughter.

“I call the police at 8pm and they knock on my door at 3am,” she recalled. “Nothing was ever resolved.”

When asked for comment by Express.co.uk, the Metropolitan Police said they could not comment without more details about when and where the crime took place.

Jessie's daughter's father, Dave Morgan, worked as a policeman when they were together.

The couple first got together in 2003 but called off their engagement and split before their daughter was born.

Jessie is currently dating greengrocer Paul Krepin, 40, after they were first romantically linked in October.

Last month, the pair made a rare public appearance when they stepped out together for the press night of Everybody’s Talking About Jamie in London.

The mother-of-one looked in high spirits as she accompanied her beau to the show, which stars EastEnders favourite Shane Richie, 55.

Jessie first shot to fame playing Kat in EastEnders, joining the cast in 2000.

She appeared on the soap until 2005 and later returning in 2010.

Following six more years on the show, she departed once again in 2016 but made her dramatic comeback to Walford last year.

Her time as Kat has earned the actress numerous awards, including Most Popular Newcomer at the National Television Awards in 2001 and the British Soap Award for Best Actress in 2011.

In addition to her role on EastEnders, Jessie has also appeared in the likes of Wild at Heart and The Bill.

EastEnders continues tonight at 8pm on BBC One.
